Video 1

Loss on training data large: Model Bias (need a more complex model) or Optimization
Loss on testing data large: Overfitting or mismatch -> more data

Video 2

How to Optimize:
L(θ)≈L(θ′)+(θ−θ′)Tg→+12(θ−θ′)TH(θ−θ′)
Gradient g→:
g→=∇L(θ′)
gi=∂L(θ′)∂θi
g→=[∂L∂θ1∂L∂θ2⋮∂L∂θn]
Hessian H is a matrix Hij=∂2L(θ′)∂θi∂θj
For all v:

  1. vTHv>0: H is positive definite, L(θ)>L(θ′): Local minima
  2. vTHv<0: H is negative definite, L(θ)<L(θ′): Local maxima
  3. Some eigenvalues are +, some are −: Saddle point
    Empirical learning:

  1. Adagrad
  2. RMSProp
  3. Adam: RMSProp + Momentum

Learning rate Decay
Warm up (Residual Network, Transformer Classification)

Video 5

Regression:
Right answer: y^↔y
Classification: class: one-hot vector: y^↔y′=softmax(y)
Soft-max (Normalize): n≥3: yi′=exp⁡(yi)∑jexp⁡(yj)
n=2 y′=sigmoid(y)

Distance e:
Mean Square Error (MSE): e=∑(yi^−yi′)2
Cross-entropy: e=−∑yi^ln⁡yi′
Minimize Cross-entropy ↔ Maximize likelihood

Video 4

Maximum likelihood Estimation:
Pdata(x) True Distribution of Data
Pθ(x) Probability distribution of data x given parameters θ
{x1,x2,⋯,xm} Observed data samples

Network: z→θ→Pθ(x)→Pdata(x)
maximize Pθ(x1)Pθ(x2)⋯Pθ(xm)

θ∗=arg⁡maxθlog⁡Pθ(x1)Pθ(x2)⋯Pθ(xm)

θ∗=arg⁡maxθEx∼Pdatalog⁡Pθ(x)

θ∗=arg⁡maxθ∫xPdata(x)log⁡Pθ(x)dx

θ∗=arg⁡maxθ(∫xPdata(x)log⁡Pθ(x)dx−∫xPdata(x)log⁡Pdata(x)dx)

θ∗=arg⁡maxθ∫xPdata(x)log⁡Pθ(x)Pdata(x)dx

θ∗=arg⁡maxθ−KL(Pdata||Pθ)

VAE

Compute Pθ(x)
Network: G(z)=x
Pθ(x)=∫Pθ(x|z)Pθ(z)dz

Pθ(z|x)=Pθ(x|z)Pθ(z)Pθ(x)

DDPM

Video 5

VAE: Variational Auto-encoder
Pθ(x)=∫Pθ(x|z)Pθ(z)dz
Pθ(z|x)=Pθ(x|z)Pθ(z)Pθ(x)

VAE

https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1yD4y1i7Jm/?p=44&vd_source=441679270dda23308fe16f3c5602b058
https://www.cnblogs.com/wxkang/p/17128108.html
比较主流的生成模型：HMM, NB, GMM (Gaussian Mixture Model)

KL divergence: KL(P||Q)=∫P(x)log⁡P(x)Q(x)dx, KL(P||Q)≠KL(Q||P)

AE: 与 PCA, SVD 目的相同，矩阵降维技术。

latent variable z, assume it follows the prior distribution of P(z)∼N(0,1)

P(x|z)∼N(μ(z),σ(z))

P(x)=∫P(z)P(x|z)dz

To Maximize Likelihood of observed x: L=∑xlog⁡P(x)

ELBO Evidence Lower Bound

Monte Carlo Integration

If X is uniformly distributed on [a,b]:
∫abf(x)dx=∫abf(x)1b−adx=Ex∼U(a,b)[f(x)]=1N∑i=1Nf(xi)

If we know the distribution of X on [a,b]=p(x):
∫abf(x)dx=∫abf(x)p(x)p(x)dx=Ex∼p(x)[f(x)]=1N∑i=1Nf(xi)p(xi)

Acceptance-Rejection Sampling

https://blog.quantitations.com/inference/2012/11/24/rejection-sampling-proof

方便采样的常用概率分布函数 (proposal distribution) q(x) 以及一个常量 k 使得 p(x) 总在 kq(x) 的下方
